<text>ENERGY GAMES:  A molecular playground

Two atoms
Here are two atoms near each other. 
This is about the simplest possible model, but if you look closely there is a lot to learn. 
Guess what happens when you run this model. 
Here is a hint: all atoms attract each other. 
The blue arrows show the force on each atom. 

  

Check this box and run the model:   
When this is checked, the shade of red indicates kinetic energy.
Note how the kintetic energy changes as the atoms approach. 

The model is very slow, so you can observe it. 
Let it run for a few minutes while you watch it very carefully. 
If you understand the model you can answer these questions. 
      
      
      
      
      

Let&apos;s speed up the model a bit so things can get more interesting. 
Go to next model--&gt;

</text>
